	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I figured out the problem. It was certainly a straight forward thing to fix.... XD.<br /><br />My CPU was polling for interrupts incorrectly, so the NMI was being fired at the wrong time. I made sure interrupts were polled just before the last cycle of every instruction. Also checked that the dummy reads / writes, page crossings and branch timings were correctly implemented. That solved it. <br /><br />Â¡Gracias Nostromo!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
